commentTextItems.html: full toss on the off stump. Hussey, lofts it high over mid-on and it bounces on the ropes. Thus Hussey finishes the match off in style

commentPostTextItems.html: Hussey brothers make sure that the series goes to Brisbane with everything to play for. They were helped in good part by Haddin too

After the dismissal of Haddin, it seemed that the Kiwis had the upper hand but the partnership between the Hussey brothers dashed all the hopes of a victory and it will be all down to the final match in Brisbane on Friday. Hold on for a few minutes for the presentation
Michael Hussey compliments Ferguson for his coolness under pressure and also compliments his brother on his good knock.
Vettori says "It was disappointing not to get to a total we expected. It will be everything to play for in Brisbane. It will be pretty exciting"
Ponting is happy that his bowlers did a good job in restricting the Kiwi batsmen bar the batting Powerplay and is pretty appreciative of Michael Hussey and Michael Clarke.
David Hussey is the Man of the match and he admits he was nervous after the Haddin dismissal. He is thankful that his brother calmed the nerves and allowed him a free hand.
Join us on Friday for the decider in Brisbane. Till then, good night from all of us at Cricinfo

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Mills b Bracken 23 (27b 1x4 1x6 42m) SR: 85.18

dismissalComment.html: timber! Mills is backing away even before the ball is bowled. Bracken notices it and bowls a yorker on the middle stump. Mills has a swing and there is only place where the ball can go- stumps- if he misses and it does go there

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin run out (Cumming/†McCullum) 43 (67b 5x4 1x6 101m) SR: 64.17

dismissalComment.html: short outside the off stump. Hussey, cuts it to deep point and Haddin, wants a couple. Hussey, initially responds and shouts a loud no as Haddin is on the run. Haddin has to run back and he is not quick enough to beat Cumming's throw. Kiwis are right on top here

headshotImage.caption: Peter Fulton player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Peter Fulton player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke c Fulton b O'Brien 14 (19b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 73.68

dismissalComment.html: and the bowling change works! O'Brein bowls one on the off stump. Clarke, drives it on the up and ends up spooning an easy catch to Fulton at short cover. Fulton, has been an exceptional fielder close-in

dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting c Guptill b Southee 15 (27b 2x4 0x6 37m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: and for the umpteenth time this summer we see Ponting top-edging a pull shot. Only difference this time being he does it to the cover fielder as Guptill takes it comfortably. Ever heard of a strength turning into a weakness
